======================================================================
PART 4: 'FORBIDDEN' CYCLE VALUES AT EACH FUGACITY
======================================================================

'Forbidden C_3 value' at each fugacity:
  k | x=k(k+1) | I(C_3,x) = (k+1)^3 + (-k)^3 = (2k+1)(k^2+k+1)
  0 |     0    |          1 = 1 x 1
  1 |     2    |          7 = 3 x 3
  2 |     6    |         19 = 5 x 7
  3 |    12    |         37 = 7 x 13
  4 |    20    |         61 = 9 x 21
  5 |    30    |         91 = 11 x 31
  6 |    42    |        127 = 13 x 43
  7 |    56    |        169 = 15 x 57
  8 |    72    |        217 = 17 x 73
  9 |    90    |        271 = 19 x 91

  PATTERN: I(C_3, k(k+1)) = 3k(k+1) + 1 = 3x + 1
  At x=2: I(C_3,2) = 7 = 3(2)+1
  At x=6: I(C_3,6) = 19 = 3(6)+1
  At x=12: I(C_3,12) = 37 = 3(12)+1
  BEAUTIFUL: the 'forbidden' C_3 value at fugacity x is always 3x+1!

  VERIFIED: I(C_3, x) = 3x + 1 for ALL x = 0..29
  (This is just 1 + 3x = I({triangle}, x) since C_3 has 3 vertices,
   3 edges, and independence sets: {}, {0}, {1}, {2} giving 1 + 3x.)
  Wait, C_3 has NO independent sets of size >= 2 (it's a triangle)!
  So I(C_3, x) = 1 + 3x exactly. Not 3k^2+3k+1!

  CORRECTION: I(C_n, x) vs alpha^n + beta^n:

  x=2: alpha=2, beta=-1
    I(C_3,2) =        7, alpha^n+beta^n =        7, match = True
    I(C_4,2) =       17, alpha^n+beta^n =       17, match = True
    I(C_5,2) =       31, alpha^n+beta^n =       31, match = True
    I(C_6,2) =       65, alpha^n+beta^n =       65, match = True
    I(C_7,2) =      127, alpha^n+beta^n =      127, match = True
    I(C_8,2) =      257, alpha^n+beta^n =      257, match = True
    I(C_9,2) =      511, alpha^n+beta^n =      511, match = True
    I(C_10,2) =     1025, alpha^n+beta^n =     1025, match = True
    I(C_11,2) =     2047, alpha^n+beta^n =     2047, match = True

  RESOLUTION: Both formulas agree!
  I(C_3, x) = 1 + 3x (from direct counting)
  I(C_3, k(k+1)) = (k+1)^3 + (-k)^3 = 3k^2+3k+1 = 3k(k+1)+1 = 3x+1
  These are THE SAME formula: 1 + 3x = 3x + 1 ✓

